   SALVADOR-NUNS (Miami) _ El Salvador's defense minister suspected
that a member of his high command had ordered the killing of four
American churchwomen in 1980 and later informed the U.S. ambassador
of his belief, according to newly released State Department
documents. By Larry Rohter.
</P>
