<P>
   OBIT-O'DWYER (Undated) _ Paul O'Dwyer, a liberal lawyer and
onetime New York City Council president who passionately championed
causes from voting rights to Irish independence, died on Wednesday
at his home in Goshen, N.Y., after a long illness, his office said.
He was 91. By Francis X. Clines.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-NORWAY-ANTHRAX (Undated) _ Lumps of sugar found in a Norway
museum contain anthrax, scientists have discovered. They were part
of a German germ warfare scheme in World War I intended to destroy
the supply lines in Northern Norway by killing reindeer and horses.
By William J. Broad.
