triumph for its long-running antitrust battle with the government.
To the Justice Department and 20 states pitted against Microsoft,
it was merely a bump in the road as they head to court again in
September with a broader antitrust case against the company. Yet
antitrust experts say the split-decision by the three-judge panel
is both a big win for Microsoft and a reflection of wider debate
over how antitrust doctrine should apply to high-technology
industries. By Steve Lohr.
