 NEWS &AMP; FEATURES SUMMARY No 2458 - JUNE 25, 1998  
<TEXT>
<P>
   1. SIGHT UNSEEN : SHOPPING BLIND In this revealing personal
reflection that is in turn sad, frustrating and funny, Carol
Fleischman discusses her own experiences shopping for a dress with
the assistance of her guide dog, Misty. Offering useful tips for
salespeople serving blind customers and favourite comments
overheard from nearby children, Fleischman provides an entirely new
outlook on something as common as the department store. From The
Buffalo News. 1,000 words + photo.
_______________________________________________________________2.
VIAGRA'S OTHER SIDE EFFECT : UPSETS IN MANY A MARRIAGE Therapists
and experts on sexuality are finding that Viagra, the popular new
drug for impotence, may actually throw into chaos some
relationships that have fallen into their own routine, sexual
dysfunction and all. By Jennifer Steinhauer. New York Times Science
Times. 1,500 words.
_______________________________________________________________3.
HAIR ANALYSIS YIELDS CLUES TO HEROIN DEATHS Hair analysis of 37
people who died from heroin overdose in Italy reveals that they had
taken little or no heroin in the months before their last injection
of the potent narcotic. The findings suggest that the risk of
heroin overdose is particularly high for addicts who go back to the
drug after quitting for a time, and for so-called 'recreational' or
'weekend' users who inject heroin only occasionally, a pattern of
heroin use that is becoming increasingly common. By Michael
McCarthy. The Lancet News Service. 1,000 words.
