THE CHAMPIONS OF GERMAN ENGINEERING The Fraunhofer institutes, a
collection of highly specialized engineering centres that combine
the theory of academia with the practice of industry, fill a unique
niche in Germany's industrial landscape. There is no industrial
problem, no matter how basic or mundane, that does not intrigue
them and the solution is likely to help make a company profitable.
By Mathias Greffrath. From GEO. 2,500 words. (English translation
available.)
