 &HT;    With FEDBUD-SURPLUS
 &HT;    c.1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WITHOUT SOCIAL SECURITY FUNDS, OPERATING BUDGET STILL IN DEFICIT
</P>
<P>
   The federal budget surplus would be a deficit in most upcoming
years if Social Security trust fund revenues were not counted:
</P>
<P>
   With revenues Without revenues
</P>
<P>
   from trust fund from trust fund
</P>
<P>
   1998 $39 billion -$63 billion
</P>
<P>
   1999 $54 billion -$59 billion
</P>
<P>
   2000 $61 billion -$62 billion
</P>
<P>
   2001 $83 billion -$48 billion
</P>
<P>
   2002 $148 billion $6 billion
</P>
<P>
   2003 $150 billion -$2 billion
</P>
