<HEADLINE>
ANGEL TAKES WINGS IN `BUFFY THE VAMPIRE SLAYER' SPINOFF
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: Where can I write to the actor who plays Angel on ``Buffy the
Vampire Slayer''?
</P>
<P>
   _ T.M.D., Arlington, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: Write to David Boreanaz and any other member of the ``Buffy''
cast in care of Buffy the Vampire Slayer, Warner Bros. Television
Network, 4000 Warner Blvd., Burbank, Calif. 91522.
</P>
<P>
   Although Angel met an unpleasant demise in the season finale,
the character will be returning. WB has ordered 13 episodes of a
new ``Angel'' spinoff series for fall 1999.
</P>
<P>
   ``Buffy'' was the first starring role for Boreanaz, who
previously appeared in an episode of ``Married ... With Children''
and the movies ``Men Don't Lie'' and ``Eyes of the World.''
</P>
<P>
   The 27-year-old actor is a Philadelphia native and a film
studies graduate of Ithaca College.
</P>
<P>
   Q: When will the new NHL franchises in Atlanta, Minnesota,
Columbus and Nashville start playing?
</P>
<P>
   _ T.C., via the Internet
</P>
<P>
   A: The Nashville Predators are the first to start, joining the
league in the fall for the 1998 season.
</P>
<P>
   To stock the team, an expansion draft will be held June 26 in
which the Predators can select one player from each existing NHL
team. The team also picks third in the first round of the NHL entry
draft on June 27 and second in each successive round.
</P>
<P>
   The Atlanta Thrashers will begin play in the 1999 season,
followed by the Columbus Blue Jackets and Minnesota Wild in 2000.
</P>
<P>
   Q: In the Diet Pepsi commercial about the jilted bride, is the
woman played by Jeri Ryan of ``Star Trek: Voyager''?
</P>
<P>
   _ J.C., Arlington, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: The actor distracted by the taste of Diet Pepsi is Alexis
Smart, according to Pepsi spokesman Jon Harris.
</P>
<P>
   Smart, who is being considered for another Pepsi commercial, has
appeared in more than 100 ads for Doritos, Southwestern Bell, GTE
and others.
</P>
<P>
   The 25-year-old actress also had a role in the movie ``Gia.''
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
</TEXT>
