demonstrate how the game of baseball has particularly blessed New
York City this year with talent and character. An umpire will shout
a familiar demand, a Mets pitcher will fire a baseball to a Yankees
batter, and all will be right in one corner of an ever-churning
metropolis. By Dan Barry.  &QL;
