   IRAN-SOCCERSCRIBE _ TEHRAN, Iran _ For this sports reporter to
do her job, she had to break the gender barrier on Iranian soccer.
In April, Mahin Gorji became the first Iranian woman to attend a
soccer game in Iran since the Islamic revolution in 1979. She
credits the new moderate Iranian President Mohammad Khatami for
making it possible, but it's not easy being a woman sports reporter
in a country where most sporting events are segregated by gender.
(Kaplow, Cox News Service) ETA: 8 p.m.
