<P>
   NBA-DRAFT _ If the NBA college draft (and, hey, it's really a
high school/college/around-the-world draft) is so important, how
come the so-called lottery teams _ the ones with the most
advantageous positions for making selections _ look so familiar
year after year after year? Because, by deductive reasoning, the
draft isn't all that important. (Stoda, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
