<HEADLINE>
ADVERTISING NOTES 
</HEADLINE>
  (th) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   BBDO FORMS VENTURE WITH JAPANESE PARTNER
</P>
<P>
   BBDO Worldwide in New York and I&AMP;S Corp. in Tokyo said Thursday
that they would form a partnership in Japan, formalizing a
relationship that began in April when Omnicom Group, the parent of
BBDO, acquired a 20 percent interest in I&AMP;S.
</P>
<P>
   Allen Rosenshine, chairman and chief executive of BBDO, said the
deal marked the first time that a top-10 Japanese agency had
entered into an equity agreement with a Western agency in which
operations would be merged rather than held in a separate joint
venture. As BBDO begins its relationship with I&AMP;S, he added, the
agency would end, after 14 years, an association with Asatsu Inc.
in Tokyo for the Japanese market.
</P>
<P>
   I&AMP;S ranks eighth among Japanese agencies, with billings
estimated at $912 million from clients including Kao and Shiseido.
BBDO serves clients in Japan including Bayer AG and Pepsico Inc.,
which are expected to be shifted to the new partnership.
</P>
<P>
   __
</P>
<P>
   MGM GRAND PICKS YOUNG &AMP; RUBICAM
</P>
<P>
   MGM Grand Inc. in Las Vegas, the hotel and casino company backed
by billionaire Kirk Kerkorian, said Thursday that it had named the
San Francisco office of Young &AMP; Rubicam Advertising to handle its
worldwide marketing account. Billings were estimated at more than
$20 million.
</P>
<P>
   The decision, which had been expected, came after a two-month
review that had been narrowed to Y&AMP;R San Francisco and one other
finalist, Saatchi &AMP; Saatchi Los Angeles, part of Saatchi &AMP; Saatchi
PLC. The account had most recently been handled by DRGM in Las
Vegas, which resigned in February. MGM Grand plans to open
additional hotel-casinos in Atlantic City and Detroit.
</P>
<P>
   __
</P>
<P>
   PEOPLE
</P>
<P>
   _ Werner Michel, a longtime executive at Bozell Worldwide, New
York, a unit of True North Communications, is retiring after more
than 50 years in the agency and media industries. He was most
recently senior partner for national broadcast programming at BJK&AMP;E
Media.
</P>
<P>
   __
</P>
<P>
   MISCELLANY
</P>
<P>
   _ Link Exchange Inc., San Francisco, a Web site advertising
network, acquired an online commerce provider, Merchant Planet,
Minneapolis, and a Web site announcement services company, Submit
It, Boston. Terms were not disclosed. &QL;
</P>
