   &UR; GENERAL &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BROTHERS-BENNETT-NYT (Washington) _ The Bennett who defends the
president has a close and complicated relationship with the Bennett
who thinks the president should be ashamed. Each says he respects
his brother's right to make a living. By Melinda Henneberger.
</P>
<P>
   DIANA-DEATH-REVIEW-NYT _ Eight months have passed since the
Princess of Wales died in what the French authorities have called a
straightforward car crash. But their flat assertions that it was
merely an accident have only encouraged theorists, who are still
busily inventing wacky stories. By Sarah Lyall.
</P>
<P>
   PROFILE-PROULX-BOS (Surry, N.H.) _ Earl Proulx never expected to
become nationally known. But as Yankee magazine's purveyor of sound
building advice, he has. By Patti Doten.
</P>
