</P>
<P>
   `LAST DAYS'-DIRECTOR-TEX (Undated) _ At 46, ``Last Days of
Disco'' director Whit Stillman still loves the night life, he loves
the boogie, and he doesn't think either fits in well with thunking
melons. As the title of his movie indicates, Stillman is fond of
disco music, but he says it has its place, and that place is in the
clubs. Not in commercials. Not on the radio. Not in any piped-in
situation. By Robrt Philpot.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-WILKINSON-KANSAS (Kansas City) _ An interview with British
actor Tom Wilkinson, who is in Kansas City filming Ang Lee's new
Civil War film titled ``Ride with the Devil.'' Wilkinson talks
about his life before and after the Full Monty. By Robert Butler.
</P>
