   DEHAVILLAND-COX _ Her character, Melanie, may have died in the
beloved movie, but Olivia de Havilland, 81, is the last remaining
star of ``Gone With the Wind,'' which reopens in theaters June 26.
An interview with the two-time Oscar winning actress, Paris
resident, sister of Joan Fontaine and rebellious Warner Brothers
contract player, in New York.
</P>
<P>
   SHEEDY-MOVIE-LADN (Los Angeles) _ Every time Ally Sheedy drifts
on screen in the acclaimed new independent film ``High Art,'' our
attention is riveted. It's a long way from ``The Breakfast Club.''
And it's something the onetime Brat Pack star, now 36, had to go
through certain hells in order to accomplish. By Bob Strauss.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-RICCI-BOS (Undated) _ From ``The Addams Family'' to Ang
Lee's wrenching family drama, ``The Ice Storm,'' Christina Ricci
has always brought an unsettling maturity and tangy flavor to her
roles. With her world-weary eyes and deadpan delivery, she is
making a far smoother transition from child to adult roles than,
say, Macaulay Culkin. By Renee Graham.
</P>
