<HEADLINE>
FOR HASEK, A 3-AWARD NIGHT  
(JT)
</HEADLINE>
   c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   TORONTO _ On Thursday night, for the second consecutive season,
Dominik Hasek of the Sabres won both the Hart and Vezina trophies
as the most valuable player and best goalie in the National Hockey
League. He also won the Lester Pearson award, a most valuable
player trophy from fellow players.
</P>
<P>
   Sergei Samsonov of the Boston Bruins won the Calder trophy as
rookie of the year. ``Dad, this one is for you,'' he said. Rob
Blake of Los Angeles won the Norris trophy for best defenseman.
Jere Lehtinen of Dallas won the Selke for best defensive forward.
Pat Burns of Boston took the Adams trophy as coach of the year. The
Lady Byng, for sportsmanship and skill, went to Ron Francis of
Pittsburgh.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
