<HEADLINE>
EXCERPT FROM CATHOLIC-LUTHERAN DECLARATION ON SALVATION 
</HEADLINE>
  (th) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Following is an excerpt from a Catholic and Lutheran declaration
on salvation:
</P>
<P>
   All persons depend completely on the saving grace of God for
their salvation. The freedom they possess in relation to persons
and the things of this world is no freedom in relation to
salvation, for as sinners they stand under God's judgment and are
incapable of turning by themselves to God to seek deliverance, of
meriting their justification before God, or of attaining salvation
by their own abilities. Justification takes place solely by God's
grace. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
