u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-GLF-LPGA-SHOPRITE-NYT     06-25 0197
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GLF-LPGA-SHOPRITE-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LPGA MAKES STOP IN NEW JERSEY 
</HEADLINE>
  (th) 
 By ALEX YANNIS    
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Those Ladies Professional Golf Association players who competed
in the ShopRite Classic the last time it was held at Absecon, N.J.,
11 years ago will find that everything old is new again. The
Marriott Resort Bay course to which the tournament has returned has
undergone substantial renovations since it was last staged there in
1987.
</P>
<P>
   After the original blueprints of the Donald Ross-designed course
were found a few years ago, the resort decided to return the course
to its 1914 look.
</P>
<P>
   The small greens have been expanded without losing their
undulating surfaces and a number of holes have been put in their
original order. Over the years, members had changed the way the
course was played.
</P>
<P>
   In the 11 years in which the tournament was staged down the road
in Somers Point, it has gone from a tournament without a sponsor
and the smallest purse to the richest three-day event on the Ladies
Professional Golf Association tour. The three-day event, which
begins Friday, is now a $1 million tournament with $150,000 going
to the winner. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
