<SLUG> BC-NY-CHEF-RESIGN-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CHEF LEAVING LESPINASSE 
</HEADLINE>
  (lb) 
 By FLORENCE FABRICANT   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Gray Kunz, the chef at Lespinasse, the luxury
restaurant in the St. Regis Hotel, has announced that he is leaving
the restaurant. His last day will be July 25.
</P>
<P>
   Kunz, 42, whose Asian-accented French fare has earned a
four-star rating from The New York Times, said he was hoping to
open his own restaurant in Manhattan. ``A lot of chefs aspire and
dream to own their own place, and I'm no different,'' he said.
``But I feel I need time to reflect. If the people who say they
want to do a restaurant with me are sincere, they will be there for
me in a few months.''
</P>
<P>
   He said his leaving had nothing to do with a union dispute and
brief walkout that occurred last fall, during which Kunz left the
restaurant for almost three weeks. Nor was it related to the change
in ownership of the hotel, Kunz and a spokesman for the St. Regis
said. ITT-Sheraton sold the St. Regis to Starwood Hotels and
Resorts of White Plains last year.
</P>
<P>
   Christian Delouvrier, the chef at Les Celebrites, the three-star
restaurant in the Essex House, will succeed Kunz.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
